    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="308"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d308">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">New London, Conn.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-08-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I am in
                    receipt of a dispatch from Her Majesty’s secretary of state for foreign affairs
                    acquainting me that Mr. Haggard, Her Majesty’s minister at Caracas, has accepted
                    the courteous offer of Mr. Loomis, the United States minister at that capital,
                    to allow the United States consul at La Guayra to take temporary charge of the
                    British vice-consulate there.</p>
                <p>I am instructed by the Marquis of Salisbury to convey to your Government the
                    thanks of Her Majesty’s Government for Mr. Loomis’s action in the matter.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
